-- MetLife says U.S. regulators declared it 'systemically' important
-- By Emily Stephenson
-- Thu Dec 18, 2014 04:17PM EST
-- None



WASHINGTON, Dec 18 (Reuters) - MetLife <MET.N> said on Thursday it has been notified by U.S. regulators that it has been declared so big that its failure could destabilize financial markets, a designation that brings extra regulation.

